KijiHTablePool This private class is designed to serve as a replacement for HTablePool, to get around the following HBase issues in the face of master failures: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6580 https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6956 https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4805 We accomplish this by creating a simple pool and a Pooled implementation of HTableInterface, similar to how HTablePool works.
 

Package org.kiji.schema.impl.hbase Description

Implementations for the main KijiSchema classes and interfaces.

Users generally shouldn't need to reference any of these classes directly, but rather use the classes presented by the org.kiji.schema package.
